      "date": "2015-01-15 20:58:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nmake rpms fails:\n\nerror: File not found: /root/kernel/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/lustre-2.6.92-2.6.32_431.20.3.el6_lustre.x86_64_g9db548f.x86_64/usr/lib64/libptlctl.a\nerror: File not found: /root/kernel/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/lustre-2.6.92-2.6.32_431.20.3.el6_lustre.x86_64_g9db548f.x86_64/usr/lib64/libcfsutil.a\n\n\nI think I solved a similar issue in the previous patch lu-5541.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e658043cbfbec9561e59a9d9dd786567d51796d7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-15 21:43:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNeed to install the libcfsutil.la instead. Once thing I can't figure out why several of the applications now want libreadline when built against liblustreapi.so. liblustreapi.so is not built against libreadline.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "457e123014ac0feec3cb95a8793587fd934d875e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-15 22:53:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIs there a need to provide these two libraries at all? The rpm doesn't contain a header for the functions they provide.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1a70f041c9669729c884c5044a34de14cae2381f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-15 23:05:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe readline dependency comes from libcfsutil. You should remove that line:\n\n\nliblustreapi_la_LIBADD = $(LIBCFS)\n\n\nand then add $(LIBCFS) where it is needed. e.g.:\n\nlfs_LDADD := liblustreapi.la $(LIBPTLCTL) $(LIBCFS) $(LIBREADLINE)\n\nlfs_DEPENDENCIES := $(LIBPTLCTL) $(LIBCFS) liblustreapi.la",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "76505c962828a4f0c30f5af1dc245d5ea9d2a8b5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 301,
        "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
        "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
        "username": "dmiter",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-01-16 11:26:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAll symbols from libcfsutil.la are inside liblustreapi.a now. So, there is no need to have it separately.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
