      "date": "2015-01-19 15:56:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nliblustreapi should not depend on or include libcfsutil.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "79ea1e72e93ed46b879d48de269807264d8306f6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-19 16:07:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nFor liblustreapi.so to be independent of libcfs.a or libcfsutil.a then all uses of strlcpy and friends need to be removed. Currently liblustreapi.so has to be used with libcfs.a since it uses the functions strlcpy.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "390d620a5a3661dbd662b8edfdc8d5515183c487",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-19 16:12:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI'm not sure if you're agreeing or disagreeing with me.\n\nliblustreapi should not depend on or include libcfsutil.\n\nliblustreapi should include libcfs.a unless libc provides strl{cat,cpy}().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "77fd9271ddb1634d66da1d541ab6a5dfb43e2dc7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-19 18:09:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI'm saying libcfs.a dependency of liblustreapi.so is wrong. Since Lustre is a linux only product and strlcpy is not support on linux it should be removed and replaced by the standard strncpy. Also as Zago pointed out have our own strlcpy will conflict with applications that link against libbsd.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "2f7911f6d0f5e306f636b96bb3f9f45a04681951",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-02-03 16:32:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWorking on a cleanup.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
